
[1]alterative

   AL'TERATIVE, a. Causing alteration; having the power to alter.

   AL'TERATIVE, n. A medicine which, without sensible operation, gradually
   induces a change in the habit or constitution and restores healthy
   functions. This word is more generally used than alterant.
